<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-603-943  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 603 943.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Nov 1990 v27 n11 p28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T plant gears for just-in-time control.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Conser, Rod.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ATandamp;T's Omaha Works produces electronic wire and cabling,connection and protection systems and sheetmetal products for thecorporation's Network Cable Systems business.andP;  When a network wasneeded to reduce product-realization cycles and move towardjust-in-time (JIT) inventory control, both coax and fibersolutions were considered.andP;  ATandamp;T's Systimax Premises DistributionSystem (PDS) fiber-based network was selected, along with thefirm's ST connectors, to provide immunity from bothelectromagnetic and radio-frequency interference.andP;  Systimax PDSsupported data, voice, graphics, video and security sensor signalsover an integrated, multifunctional system wiring plan thatincorporates fiber optic and twisted-pair cable, along withconnectors and adaptors.andP;  Modular access to the backbonesimplifies the rerouting of traffic.andP;  The system is used to ensurethe availability of correct manufacturing instructions, to controlthe flow of materials, to monitor employee attendance, and tosupport satellite television and plant security cameras.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   AT and T Omaha Works (Communication systems).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Just In Time Inventory SystemsFiber optics.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Premises distribution system information network. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>